               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1300">S. XIV</origDate>
                     <origPlace><country key="place_1000070">France</country></origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Made in France. </provenance>
                  <provenance>On f. 340v, is ‘Liber m. <persName key="person_96800842" role="fmo">Symonis Bredon</persName>’ doctoris in medicina quondam socii domus de Merton’ in Oxon’’, s. xv ex. Simon Bredon (<title>BRUO</title> 257–8) was fellow in 1330, still in 1341, canon of Chichester, d. 1372. This book is not among those mentioned in his will (pr. Powicke, pp. 82–6). </provenance>
                  <provenance>Inside the front board is a sheet of paper with titles and ‘P. 2. 6. Art:’, s. xvii, the latter canc. and replaced with ‘N. 3. 6’ and ‘No. CCXXIII’ in red; the College bookplate. ‘6’ is inked on the foredge.</provenance>
               </history>
